cdn.com/app/cms/image/transf/dimension=2080x10000:format=jpg/path/s2217cd0bb1220415/image/i924c52c240be26ee/version/1683854111/the-forbidden-city-beijing.jpg'),(44,'Yellow Mountain (Huangshan)',9,'Yellow Mountain, or Huangshan, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site known for its unique granite peaks, ancient pine trees, and mystical atmosphere. Experience the breathtaking sunrise over the sea of clouds, hike through scenic trails, and appreciate the timeless beauty that has inspired traditional Chinese art and literature for centuries.','UNESCO World Heritage Site, Granite peaks, Ancient pine trees, Breathtaking sunrise, Sea of clouds, Scenic trails, Huangshan','https://www.mercierzeng.com/image/huangshan/yellow-mountains-19.jpg'),(45,'Terracotta Army, Xi\'an',9,'The Terracotta Army in Xi\'an is a remarkable archaeological discovery, featuring thousands of life-sized clay soldiers and horses buried with Emperor Qin Shi Huang. Explore the three pits containing the terracotta warriors, each with its own formations and details. Witness the incredible craftsmanship and historical significance of this UNESCO World Heritage Site.','Archaeological discovery, Life-sized clay soldiers, Emperor Qin Shi Huang, Three pits, Craftsmanship, Historical significance, Xi\'an','https://assets.editorial.aetnd.com/uploads/2014/03/gettyimages-1236172686.jpg?width=768'),(46,'Chichen Itza',10,'Chichen Itza, a UNESCO World Heritage Site on the Yucatan Peninsula, is a mesmerizing archaeological complex that was once a major city of the ancient Maya civilization. Explore the iconic El Castillo pyramid, marvel at the astronomical precision of the structures, and discover the rich history and cultural significance of Chichen Itza. With its captivating ruins and historical importance, Chichen Itza offers a fascinating journey into the mysteries of the Maya civilization.','UNESCO World Heritage Site, Ancient Maya civilization, El Castillo pyramid, Astronomical precision, Archaeological complex, Yucatan Peninsula, Historical significance','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/51/Chichen_Itza_3.jpg'),(47,'Tulum',10,'Tulum, located along the Riviera Maya, is a coastal paradise with ancient Mayan ruins overlooking the Caribbean Sea. Explore the well-preserved archaeological site, relax on pristine beaches, and snorkel in crystal-clear cenotes. Tulum offers a perfect blend of history, nature, and relaxation in a breathtaking tropical setting.','Ancient Mayan ruins, Caribbean Sea, Pristine beaches, Snorkeling, Riviera Maya, Cenotes, Tropical paradise','https://a.cdn-hotels.com/gdcs/production73/d1624/45ab7e53-4363-41f8-8783-78765ac502ee.jpg'),(48,'Cancun',10,'Cancun, a world-renowned resort city on the Yucatan Peninsula, is famous for its stunning beaches, vibrant nightlife, and archaeological wonders. Relax on the white sands of the Hotel Zone, explore the Mayan ruins of El Rey, and indulge in the energetic atmosphere of the city\'s clubs and restaurants. Cancun offers a perfect blend of sun, sea, and culture.','Stunning beaches, Vibrant nightlife, Archaeological wonders, Hotel Zone, Mayan ruins, El Rey, Energetic atmosphere','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Cancun_aerial_photo_by_safa.jpg/1200px-Cancun_aerial_photo_by_safa.jpg'),(49,'Puerto Vallarta',10,'Puerto Vallarta, nestled on the Pacific Coast, is a charming coastal town known for its cobblestone streets, vibrant art scene, and beautiful beaches. Explore the historic Old Town, stroll along the MalecÃ³n boardwalk, and enjoy water activities in Banderas Bay. Puerto Vallarta offers a blend of cultural richness and natural beauty.','Cobblestone streets, Vibrant art scene, Beautiful beaches, Old Town, MalecÃ³n boardwalk, Banderas Bay, Cultural richness','https://cdn.aarp.net/content/dam/aarp/travel/international/2022/08/1140-puerto-vallarta.jpg'),(50,'Palenque',10,'Palenque, nestled in the jungles of Chiapas, is an archaeological site showcasing the grandeur of the ancient Maya civilization. Explore the well-preserved temples and palaces, surrounded by lush greenery and wildlife. With its mystical ambiance and historical significance, Palenque offers a journey into the heart of Maya culture and architecture.','Archaeological site, Ancient Maya civilization, Temples, Palaces, Chiapas, Jungle, Mystical ambiance','https://res.klook.com/images/fl_lossy.progressive,q_65/c_fill,w_1280,h_853/w_79,x_14,y_14,g_south_west,l_Klook_water_br_trans_yhcmh3/activities/olr38xdasdwwvpnxtpgn/V%C3%A9Mi%E1%BB%85nX%E1%BA%BFpH%C3%A0ngV%C3%A0oC%E1%BB%ADaPalenque.jpg');
